      "description": "Offering a museum-grade 1993 Mazda RX-7 FD, featuring the iconic 13B-REW power plant with its sophisticated sequential twin-turbocharging system fully intact. This specimen retains its factory-spec double-wishbone suspension geometry and Torsen limited-slip differential, ensuring the precise turn-in and neutral handling characteristics the chassis is renowned for. The five-speed manual transmission delivers crisp engagement through every gate, paired with a documented service history confirming optimal rotor compression and zero vacuum leaks. The exterior maintains its original luster with perfect panel gaps and all factory VIN tags present, while the undercarriage remains free of oxidation. A rare opportunity for the purist seeking a mechanically flawless apex predator of the golden era of Japanese engineering.",
